article.headline: Hampton 82, S. Carolina St. 76
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Rashad West scored 21 points and Hampton remained unbeaten in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference with a 82-76 win over South Carolina State on Saturday. Matthew Pilgrim added 16 points for the Pirates (9-6, 4-0 MEAC), who raced out to a 15-point first-half lead and withstood a second-half surge from the Bulldogs (5-12, 1-2). Jason Flagler scored a career-high 27 points and Carrio Bennett added 17 for South Carolina State, which got within 62-58 on Bennett's 3 with 8:22 left. Pilgrim's tip-in sparked an 11-5 run that put Hampton back in control. The Pirates hit 33 of 44 free throws in their fourth straight win.
